# Trominal Filament Admin Panel

Full skill: [filament-admin.md](mdc:.ai/skills/filament-admin.md)

## Mental model

Filament is the **operator's control panel**, not a user feature. End-users live in the client app. The admin panel manages the instance.

URL: `/admin`. Required role: `admin`. 2FA required.

## Mandatory rules

### 1. Every Resource and Page MUST gate access

```php
public static function canViewAny(): bool
{
    return auth()->user()?->can('admin.users.manage') ?? false;
}
```

Forgetting this = critical security bug. Defense in depth: panel-level middleware + resource-level guards + Policies.

### 2. Every state-changing action MUST write an audit log entry

```php
Action::make('suspend')
    ->action(function ($record) {
        DB::transaction(function () use ($record) {
            $record->update(['suspended_at' => now()]);
            AuditLog::record(auth()->user(), 'admin.user.suspended', 'user', $record->id);
        });
    })
```

### 3. Self-foot-gun prevention

Don't let admins:
- Delete themselves
- Demote themselves to non-admin if they're the only admin
- Remove the last admin's `admin` role

```php
public static function canDelete(Model $record): bool
{
    if ($record->id === auth()->id()) return false;
    if ($record->hasRole('admin') && User::role('admin')->count() <= 1) return false;
    return auth()->user()->hasRole('admin');
}
```

### 4. Never expose sensitive columns in tables

Forbidden in any Filament TextColumn / display:
- `password`
- `two_fa_secret_enc`
- `private_key_*`
- Refresh tokens
- API tokens
- Vault ciphertexts

## Required v0.1 resources

- `UserResource` — list/edit/suspend, role assignment, password reset
- `RoleResource` — CRUD roles, assign permissions
- `PermissionResource` — read-only list (permissions are seeded)
- `InviteResource` — generate/revoke invite codes
- `AuditLogResource` — read-only filterable log

## Required v0.1 pages

- `Settings` — registration mode toggle, instance name, feature flags
- `SystemHealth` — queue/Redis/DB/Reverb status

## What admin panel does NOT do

- ❌ Decrypt user vaults (server can't anyway, don't try)
- ❌ Show terminal session content
- ❌ Bypass 2FA
- ❌ Manage personal user resources (hosts, snippets) — those are user-private
- ❌ Allow self-modification that could lock out the instance

## Patterns

Settings persistence via `AppSetting::value()` and `AppSetting::set()` — cached via `Cache::rememberForever`, busted on update.

Role/permission UI uses Spatie `relationship('roles', 'name')` Filament integration.

Custom pages use `protected static string $view = 'filament.pages.<name>';` and a Blade view.

## Tests required

- Non-admin gets 403 from every admin URL
- Admin can list every resource
- Cannot delete self
- Cannot delete last admin
- Audit log entry created for every state-changing action
